<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-228-956  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 228 956.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  May 1 1989 v10 n18 p31(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mainframe text-retrieval brought to the desktop.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mahnke, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Infodata Systems Inc has announced its plans to significantlybroaden text management applications by extending them to thedesktop through microcomputers and through the integration of bothimages and data from relational data bases with text.andO;Specifically, Infodata will link its Inquire-Text system to thedesktop for cooperative processing text-retrieval applications;develop a compound document strategy to include images with text;and connect its text-retrieval data base with data held in IBM'sDB2 and SQL-DS via Structured Query Language (SQL).andP;  Threeenhancements will be released by Infodata by the end of 1989 todemonstrate its long-term strategy of widening the applicabilityof text management and establishing a broader user base.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Infodata Systems Inc. (planning).andO;Ticker:    INFD.andO;Topic:     Software MigrationInformation Storage and RetrievalText Data BasesRelational Data BasesEnhancementsApplications ProgrammingIntegrated Voice-DataSearching.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>